/-- The ring of integers of a number field is not a field. -/
theorem not_is_field [number_field K] : ¬IsField ((ring_of_integers) K) :=
  by
  have h_inj : function.injective («expr⇑ » (algebra_map ℤ ((ring_of_integers) K))) :=
    RingHom.injective_int (algebra_map ℤ ((ring_of_integers) K))
  intro hf
  exact int.not_is_field (((is_integral_closure.is_integral_algebra ℤ K).is_field_iff_is_field h_inj).mpr hf)
#align not_is_field not_is_field

theorem map_mem {F L : Type _} [Field L] [CharZero K] [CharZero L] [alg_hom_class F (exprℚ) K L] (f : F)
    (x : (ring_of_integers) K) : f x ∈ (ring_of_integers) L :=
  (mem_ring_of_integers _ _).2 <| map_is_integral_int f <| ring_of_integers.is_integral_coe x

    is_integral ℤ (⟨x, hx⟩ : (ring_of_integers) K) :=
